Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora at neck join, or possibly shoulder join. Clay medium red-beige. Rectangular stamp.
Type series: KT269 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Worn pencil. Names Lysanias, Aristokrates. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0278)
